Google has announced that Cyberpunk 2077 will launch on its Stadia cloud gaming platform. CD Projekt RED’s upcoming cyberpunk-themed role-playing game is expected to launch on 16 April 2020, although there has been no confirmation that it will be available on Stadia on the date of its release. Google Stadia is expected to go live in November 2019, offering users the ability to stream popular titles including Mortal Kombat 11, Borderlands 3, Destiny 2, and Doom Eternal. Stadia’s Founder’s Edition package is priced at $129, which users can now pre-order bundled with a Chromecast Ultra. The Founder’s Edition also includes three months of Stadia Pro and a limited-edition Night Blue Stadia controller.